            <h2 id="section1Title">What We Do</h2>
            <p id="section1Text">TravelPayComparison is a free calculator that helps you compare payment methods when traveling in Japan. We calculate the actual cost of using cash, credit cards, or IC cards (like Suica), including hidden fees and exchange rate markups.</p>

            <h2 id="section2Title">Why We Built This</h2>
            <p id="section2Text">Traveling in Japan is amazing, but payment options can be confusing. Should you use cash? Credit card? Suica? Each method has different fees and exchange rates. We created this tool to make the decision simple and help you save money.</p>

            <h2 id="section3Title">How It Works</h2>
            <p id="section3Text">Enter the amount in Japanese Yen you want to spend, select your home currency, and we'll show you the real cost of each payment method. Our calculator includes typical fees for cash exchange (3%), credit card foreign transaction fees (3%), and IC card markups (1.5%).</p>

            <h2 id="section4Title">Our Recommendations</h2>
            <p id="section4Text">We recommend payment services like Wise, Revolut, and Klook based on their value to travelers. We earn commissions from affiliate links, but this doesn't affect the calculator results or our recommendations. We only recommend services we believe provide real value.</p>

            <h2 id="section5Title">Data Sources</h2>
            <p id="section5Text">Exchange rates are based on mid-market rates as of April 2026. Fees are typical market rates and may vary by provider. Always verify current rates with your payment provider before making financial decisions.</p>

            <h2 id="section6Title">Feedback</h2>
            <p id="section6Text">We're constantly improving this tool. If you have suggestions, questions, or feedback, please contact us at: hello@travelpaycomparison.com</p>

            <div class="highlight" style="margin-top: 30px;">
                <p id="thankyou">Thank you for using TravelPayComparison. Have a great trip to Japan! 🇯🇵</p>
            </div>
        </main>

        <footer>
            <p>© 2024 TravelPayComparison</p>
